               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440101-name-470" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440101-name-470" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440101-name-470" type="surname" value="TAYLOR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440101-name-470" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY TAYLOR</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Elm-place, Pimlico—I know the prisoner by sight—last Sunday, about five o'clock, be came to me, and said, "Go and get me half an ounce of tobacco, and I will give you a halfpenny"—he gave me half-a-crown to pay for it—I went with it to Mr. Norman—I gave him the half-crown—he gave it back to me—I took it to the prisoner, and said, "Mr. Nor<lb></lb>man says this is a bad one"—I gave him back the same half-crown.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440101-name-471" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440101-name-471" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440101-name-471" type="surname" value="NORMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440101-name-471" type="given" value="FREDERICK"></interp>FREDERICK NORMAN</persName>
                  </hi>, <hi rend="italic">tobacconist, Queen-street, Pimlico.</hi> About five o'clock last Sunday, Taylor came to me—he threw down a half-crown—I rubbed it on a piece of stone—it was bad, and I returned it to him—this is the same.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
